The paper discusses sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as machine translation, text summarization, and speech recognition. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses deep neural networks, which are a fundamental component of sequence-to-sequence models, making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.DL (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses reinforcement learning (RL) methods, which are used to address problems with seq2seq models, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories.
